               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-390" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-390" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-390" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-390" type="given" value="WILLIAM HENRY"></interp>WILLIAM HENRY THOMPSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an attorney's clerk, and live in Upper Weymouth-terrace, Hackney-road. On the 10th of August, be<lb></lb>tween seven and eight o'clock, I was in High-street, Shoreditch—I felt a hand touch me—I turned round and saw the prisoner's hand underneath my coat—I immediately collared him, held him till a policeman came op, and gave him into custody—I had hold of a friend's arm at the time—when I turned round I entirely lost sight of his hand for half a mi<lb></lb>nute, and when I turned my head again I saw nay handkerchief lying im<lb></lb>mediately behind him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390916-name-391" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390916-name-391" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
